benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: POST Valid Payload: Coverage includes successful transfers with minimum required fields (TC01) and transfers with all optional parameters (TC02).
Policy Variants: Scenarios cover START_OF_TERM, END_OF_TERM and IMMEDIATE policies (TC03).
Date Handling: Transfer with requestedDate today (TC04).
Edge Cases - PluginProperty: Handling multiple values (TC05) and empty array (TC18).
Error Handling: 404s for not found (TC06, TC22) and 404 for missing target account (TC07).
Invalid Input Validation: bundleId format (TC08), requestedDate format (TC09), billingPolicy value (TC10).
Missing/Invalid Input: Missing required header (TC11) and missing request body (TC12).
Recovery/Resilience: Recovery from transient network failure (TC17) and dependency unavailability (TC14, 503).
Error Codes Coverage: Server errors including 400, 404, 500, 503 mapped to scenarios (TC09, TC10, TC12, TC14, TC24).
Performance & Load: Normal/peak response times (TC27, TC28) and concurrency (TC29) and resource usage (TC30).
Backward Compatibility: Missing optional fields scenario supported (TC26).
Accessibility: Documentation and error messages accessibility (TC31).
gaps: Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests for rate-limiting behavior (e.g., 429) under high request rate.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or client caching behavior.
Duplicate Submissions: No idempotency/duplicate-transfer test scenario.
Forbidden Access: No test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient privileges (only 400/401 covered).
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify handling of rapid successive requests (expect 429 or appropriate status).
Add tests for caching headers and behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) on POST responses.
Add a dedicated test for duplicate submissions to confirm idempotency or handle duplicates gracefully.
Consider introducing a dedicated test for 202 Accepted if the operation is asynchronous (or confirm 201 semantics).
